    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1951-04-19T17:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1951-04-19T17:00:00-05:00" n="283"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d283">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">320.2–AC/4–1951: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">United States Mission at the United Nations</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1951-04-19T17:00:00-05:00"
                            >April 19, 1951—5 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>863. Dept commends ur efforts in <gloss target="#t_AMC1">AMC</gloss> Subctee and
                    suggests you continue to press for <gloss target="#t_AMC1">AMC</gloss>
                    recommendation to <gloss target="#t_GA1">GA</gloss> along lines position paper
                    Apr 12. Pls broaden consultations to include those members of <gloss
                        target="#t_AMC1">AMC</gloss> not represented on Subctee submitting US points
                    in form which wld make it possible for them to obtain authorization from their
                    Govts to proceed. <gloss target="#t_FYI1">FYI</gloss> Dept now preparing
                    approaches to UK, Fr and Australia with view to obtaining early <gloss
                        target="#t_AMC1">AMC</gloss> action.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
